title: General Chemistry Laboratory I
yc_attrs: This course can be applied towards the Sciences Yale College distributional requirement.
description:
An introduction to basic chemistry laboratory methods. Techniques required for quantitative analysis of thermodynamic processes and the properties of gases.

To accompany or follow CHEM 161 or 163. May not be taken after a higher-numbered laboratory course.
regnotes: Students must sign up for laboratory sections using the Preference Selection tool.Please be sure to select three sections before Preference Selection closes on Tuesday, September 3 at 9:00 a.m., as otherwise a section slot cannot be guaranteed. Final section times are scheduled based on enrollment preferences from the following options: M, T, W, TH, or F, 1-5 pm.Please note that Friday laboratory sections are always over-subscribed. If you require a Friday laboratory section, please provide a reason why this is necessary. If you can fit a laboratory section into your schedule on a day other than Friday, you will be helping your peers who can only take laboratory on Friday.
